* [[aard-vark]]

===Etymology===
* First attested in 1833.
* From {{etyl|af}} {{term|aarde||earth|lang=af}}, from {{etyl|dum}} {{term|aerde|lang=dum}}, + {{etyl|af}} {{term|vark||pig|lang=af}}, from {{etyl|dum}} {{term|varken|lang=dum}}; hence "earth-pig". Early European colonists in South Africa noticed that the animal was similar to a pig, while "aarde" hints at the animal's habit of burrowing.

===Pronunciation===
{{wikisource1911Enc|Aard-vark}}
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈɑː(ɹ)dˌvɑː(ɹ)k/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/":A(r\)d%vA:(r\)k/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑɹdˌvɑɹk/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"Ar\d%vAr\k/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{zoology}} The [[mammal]] ''[[Orycteropus afer]]'', of the order ''[[Tubulidentata]]'', somewhat resembling a [[pig]], common in some parts of sub-Saharan Africa.
#: ''The aardvark burrows in the ground and feeds mostly on termites, which it catches with its long, slimy tongue.
# {{slang|particularly in the southeast|_|US}} A [[silly]] or [[credulous]] person who is prone to [[mistakes]] or [[blunders]].
#: ''I walked into the wrong bathroom like a total '''aardvark'''.''

